==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[phoca]] ‘seal’, from Greek [[φωκη]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'fəʊsʌɪn/

===Adjective===
'''phocine'''
# pertaining to a [[seal]]; seallike
#:*'''1955''': she had already yanked out of me the coveted section and retreated to her mat near her '''phocine''' mamma. — Vladimir Nabokov, ''Lolita''